project_detailISsmallplaintextbox:
Full Cat B fit out of unit 2, minimal build demolition works as first floor partitions are to be kept in place. New partitions to ground floor area. Strip out of existing Toshiba ceiling mounted split units and replace with Mitsubishi mechanical system, which includes Mitsubishi lossnay ventilation system, the new mechanical install includes new condensers located in the external plant compound. Builders works are required to form apertures for external louvres. Existing tea point to be stripped out and replaced with new layout, existing plumbing to be adapted. Two new teapoint areas to be installed in to the Ground Floor, new plumbing required here to be fed from the core. All lighting to be upgraded to LED and new floorboxes to be added to suit furniture layout. Buildersworks will be required to chase out existing slab for new power, as the buildings have no raised access flooring. Ceiling to remain as they are, with minor amendments around new mechanical installation. New roller blinds throughout Ground and First Floor. Fire alarms, access control and data are by incumbent contractors however will be managed as part of our works. 

A 70m link trench will be dug to link the two buildings with 3 way containment for access control and data.
